17 being paid by the employer in lieu of contributions by the member in
18 determining tax treatment under the Internal Revenue Code of 1986
19 and such picked up contributions shall not be includable in the
20 gross income of the member until such amounts are distributed or
21 made available to the member or the beneficiary of the member. The
22 member, by the terms of this System, shall not have any option to
23 choose to receive the contributions so picked up directly and the
24 picked up contributions must be paid by the employer to the System.
